22/12/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The Association of Medical Journalists in Romania selected the local medical community as the winner of the 2003 annual award for professional achievements. 
In a press release issued Monday (22 December), the association acknowledged the Marie Curie Hospital as the best medical institution in 2003. 
Rodica Anghel, head of the Bucharest Oncology Hospital, took the prize for manager of the year. 
Physicians Dan Gherghiceanu, Cezar Macarie and Serban Bubenek were honoured for professionalism. 
(Rompres - 22/12/03)
